            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>I. Goldman Esqre<lb/>
            Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>My judgment of your<lb/> skill <del>in the art of drawing</del> as an artist&#44; will carry with<lb/> it no weight&#44; but anyone seeing the portrait<lb/> of the late Revd Isaac Leeser&#44; that you kindly<lb/> presented to me&#44; must pronounce it excellent<lb/> in every feature lineament.<lb/></p>
            <p>I sincerely wish that your<lb/> exertions may be crowned with success&#44; for&#44;<lb/> <del>you have</del> by preserving the <hi rend="underline">true</hi> expression of a<lb/> countenance&#44; which thousands will recognize<lb/> as that of <del></del> a benefactor of his people&#44; and&#93;<lb/> a zealous servant of <del>his</del> God&#59; you have conferred a<lb/> lasting favor on <del>a whole</del> the Jewish community.<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours respectfully<lb/>
            S. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> Nissan 5628<lb/>
                March 24<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1868<lb/></p>
            
        </body>
    </text>
